text: Jackson (formerly, Botilleas, Botilleas Spring, Bottileas, Bottle Spring,All and Botellas) is the county seat of Amador County in the U.S. state of California. The population was 5,019 at the 2020 census. The city is connected to State Route 49 and State Route 88. == References == == Other websites == * Official website Category:19th-century establishments in California Category:1848 establishments in the United States Category:Cities in California Category:County seats in California Category:Settlements in Amador County, California
